main event: A civilian witness observed a single object with multiple flashing lights over Plum Tree Island, Virginia for around 1.5 hours on January 27, 1965.
interesting points: The object was approximately 75 feet across and 10-15 feet thick, with flashing red and orange lights that appeared to rotate with the object.
The object was first observed at an elevation of around 75 feet and an azimuth of 020 degrees, then climbed to an elevation of 900-1000 feet and an azimuth of 090 degrees before disappearing.
The object moved in a zigzag pattern and appeared to land on the shore for about 5 minutes before taking off again, turning north, and departing at a high rate of speed.
The witness used 20-power binoculars to observe the object, and weather conditions were clear with good visibility.
The Air Force investigator concluded the most probable cause was a Navy helicopter that was known to be in the area at the time.
sighted object: Single object with multiple flashing lights
